Brazilian Stock Movers: Banco Pine, Bradesco, Embraer, Gerdau

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-03-21T20:33:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/brazilian-stock-movers-banco-bradesco-embraer-gerdau-ogx.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 0.3 percent to 66,689.61.  Banco Bradesco SA (BBDC4)  (BBDC4 BS) advanced 0.9 percent to 31.07
reais. The bank is confident it will succeed in buying a stake
in Carrefour SA’s financial unit in  Brazil , the Financial Times
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Luiz Carlos Trabuco.  Banco Pine SA (PINE4 BS) jumped 6.5 percent to 13.21 reais,
the most since August. German bank Deutsche Investitions-und
Entwicklungsgesellschaft mbH agreed to pay at least 43.7 million
reais for 2.42 million new shares of Pine, according to a
regulatory filing.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) climbed 1.6 percent to 14.07 reais.
 Alitalia  SpA agreed to acquire 20 jets from the company, the
world’s fourth-largest airplane maker, for an undisclosed
amount. Alitalia will buy 15 Embraer 175 jets and five 190
models, according to an e-mailed statement from Embraer.  Voting shares of  Gerdau SA (GGBR4)  (GGBR3 BS) plunged 5.2 percent
to 16.02 reais, and preferred shares dropped 4.9 percent to
20.25 reais. The company plans to sell as much as 4.2 billion
reais of common and preferred shares, according to a regulatory
filing.  Tim Participacoes SA (TCSL4)  (TCSL4 BS) gained 2 percent to 6.50
reais. Deutsche Telekom AG yesterday agreed to sell its wireless
unit T-Mobile to AT&T for $39 billion to create the largest U.S.
mobile-phone company. Brazilian investors are now betting Tim
may be an acquisition candidate, said Rosangela Ribeiro, an
analyst at SLW Corretora brokerage.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
